All Hamburgian assemblages from these sites are collected on surface. The finds were scattered on sandy river terraces. The finds are date only by typology and technology. The assemblages from all sites consists only from shoulder points, one scraper and two zinkens, therefore there is not much data on core preparation techniques.

The site contains only several finds asscribed to this assemblage. Only two of them (fragment of armature and wehlen scraper) have typological features that let author to ascribe them to Federmesser group.
Almost all of these sites comes from the surface finds, and those excavated ones contain only several finds ascribed to this assemblages.
The site comes from mixed surface finds and its small part was ascribed to the Ahrensburgian technology.

Most of the sites are dated by typological-technological method, except Kabeliai 2 site wich contain C14 data. Swiderian assemblages in Lithuania are much more common, therefore there are much more stratified sites and lithic concentrations, and more finds to study lithic  technology.
